widgets_values:
the workflow is using the original image and puts noise on it (denoise value in the ksampler, the lower the more of the original image is used)

if you want to use an empty latent, the efficient loader is already setup for this, just connect the latent to the ksampler and change denoise there to 1. bypass vae encode in this case.

load cap = number of images that will be loaded, if you set it = 0 all frames will be loaded.

loading a complete video shouldnt be a problem it is just a matter of time depending on the available vram its fast or slow but shouldnt lead into outofmem errors. but i think 2048k is the max at least on my card (12gb)

if you copy a prompt from civitai be sure to check for the weights! if they are above 1.4. becaues if they are higher than that like 2 it will mess up your image. 1.35 is a good max value in both positive and negative prompts.
